## McpAdapter Default Filtering Behavior

When no options are provided, `McpAdapter` defaults to **readonly filtering**.

### How It Works

In `src/sources/mcp.ts`, the constructor defaults to `options = {}`:

```ts
constructor(client: McpLikeClient, options: McpSourceOptions = {}) {
```

The `filterTools` function then processes that empty options object:

```ts
function filterTools(tools: ToolDefinition[], options: McpSourceOptions): ToolDefinition[] {
  if (options.tools && options.tools.length > 0) {
    // ← skipped: no tools allowlist provided
  }

  const readonlyEnabled = options.readonly ?? true;  // ← defaults to true
  const base = readonlyEnabled ? tools.filter((tool) => isReadonlyTool(tool.name)) : [...tools];
  // ...
  // allow and deny are both undefined, so no further modification
}
```

### Which Tools Are Exposed

Only tools whose names start with one of these prefixes (case-insensitive) pass the `isReadonlyTool` check:

```ts
const READONLY_PREFIXES = ["get_", "list_", "search_", "read_", "fetch_", "query_", "describe_"];
```

Using the fixture data from the tests as a concrete example:

| Tool | Exposed? | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `get_patient` | ✅ | starts with `get_` |
| `list_encounters` | ✅ | starts with `list_` |
| `search_medications` | ✅ | starts with `search_` |
| `update_draft_note` | ❌ | no matching prefix |
| `delete_patient` | ❌ | no matching prefix |
| `get_sensitive_phi` | ✅ | starts with `get_` |

This is confirmed by the test in `tests/sources/mcp.test.ts`:

```ts
it("defaults to readonly filtering", async () => {
  const adapter = new McpAdapter(makeToolsClient());
  await expect(adapter.list()).resolves.toEqual([
    "get_patient",
    "get_sensitive_phi",
    "list_encounters",
    "search_medications",
  ]);
});
```

### Why

The design intent is safety by default: when the adapter is connected to an MCP client, it refuses to expose mutating tools (writes, deletes, updates) unless explicitly opted in, since the agent can only read tool metadata through the source API anyway, but the exposed tool list informs what the orchestrator agent learns about.
